<subSubSection id="99F2651FFFB6FFECFCCCFD3B4D0CFA15" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB6FFECFCCCFD3B4A87FC35" blockId="7.[801,1453,748,1508]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFCCCFD3B4AF8FCF5" box="[839,922,749,772]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Notes. –</emphasis>
In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFBFBFD3A4C2CFCF5" author="BURMAN" box="[1136,1358,748,772]" firstAuthor="BURMAN" journalOrPublisher="Amsterdam" page="235" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" refId="ref8940" refString="BURMAN, N. L. (1768). Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis. Amsterdam." title="Flora Indica: cui accedit series zoophytorum indicorum, nec non prodromus florae capensis" type="book" year="1768">BURMAN (1768: 235)</bibRefCitation>
referred to two pre-Linnaean publications and a plate. He did not mention any collector, but “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFBDEFCFA4D9CFCB5" box="[1109,1278,812,836]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
Habitat in 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFB6FFECFB46FCFB4D9CFCB5" box="[1229,1278,813,836]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Java</collectingRegion>
</emphasis>
” as locality and the Javanese vernacular name “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFB0EFC9A4C42FC95" box="[1157,1312,844,868]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Pakoe-hantam</emphasis>
”. The latter should be regarded as specimen citation (the only one in the protologue!), since this name is not mentioned in any of the cited publications.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB6FFECFCCCFC1A4CC8FB55" blockId="7.[801,1453,748,1508]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
Asingle gathering in G-PREL [G00360111] matches this specimen citation: it bears the Javanese name “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFA80FC3A4CFFFBF5" box="[1291,1437,1004,1028]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Pakoe-hantam</emphasis>
”, the mention “ 
<emphasis id="E39CEA86FFB6FFECFC30FBDB4C05FBD5" box="[955,1383,1036,1060]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
ex 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFB6FFECFC52FBDB4D68FBD5" box="[985,1034,1037,1060]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Java</collectingRegion>
hanc accepi ab H. v Santen 1758
</emphasis>
” from J. Burman’s hand, and the species name in N.L. Burman’s handwriting. The collector, Henricus van Santen (1714 – 1765), arrived in Batavia [
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFB6FFECFC7BFBBA4D5CFB75" box="[1008,1086,1132,1156]" country="Indonesia" name="Jakarta Raya" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Jakarta</collectingRegion>
] in 1747 and stayed as Head of the Surgery for the VOC until his death in 1765 (
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFA8CFB5A4CFDFB55" author="FLORIJN" box="[1287,1439,1164,1188]" firstAuthor="FLORIJN" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" pagination="34 - 38" part="36" refId="ref9178" refString="FLORIJN, P. J. (1987). Biographical notes about four plant collectors in Asia mentioned by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica (1768). Taxon 36: 34 - 38." title="Biographical notes about four plant collectors in Asia mentioned by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica (1768)" type="journal article" year="1987">FLORIJN, 1987</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB6FFECFCCCFB7B4CCEFAD5" blockId="7.[801,1453,748,1508]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFCCCFB7B4D45FB35" author="MERRILL" box="[839,1063,1196,1220]" firstAuthor="MERRILL" journalOrPublisher="Philippine J. Sci." page="336" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" pagination="329 - 388" part="19" refId="ref9969" refString="MERRILL, E. D. (1921). A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica. Philippine J. Sci. 19: 329 - 388." title="A review of the new species of plants proposed by N. L. Burman in his Flora Indica" type="journal article" year="1921">MERRILL (1921: 336)</bibRefCitation>
stated that “Burman’s actual 
<typeStatus id="0E538836FFB6FFECFAEEFB7B4CF1FB34" box="[1381,1427,1197,1221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">type</typeStatus>
is a Javan specimen”. As a single specimen from 
<collectingRegion id="132CF876FFB6FFECFA8DFB1B4C52FB15" box="[1286,1328,1229,1252]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Java</collectingRegion>
is extant in G-PREL, this citation should be considered a valid implicit lectotypification. This was overlooked by 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFB13FADA4CCAFAD5" author="WIJNANDS" box="[1176,1448,1292,1316]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="WIJNANDS" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" page="186" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" pagination="155 - 198" part="72" refId="ref10394" refString="WIJNANDS, D. O., J. HENIGER, J. F. VELDKAMP, N. FUMEAUX &amp; M. W. CALLMANDER (2017). The botanical legacy of Martinus Houttuyn (1720 - 1798) in Geneva. Candollea 72: 155 - 198." title="The botanical legacy of Martinus Houttuyn (1720 - 1798) in Geneva" type="journal article" year="2017">WIJNANDS et al. (2017: 186)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1573694FFB6FFECFCCCFAFA4D0CFA15" blockId="7.[801,1453,748,1508]" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">
Subsequent authors such as 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFBE7FAFA4C4DFAB5" author="HOLTTUM" box="[1132,1327,1324,1348]" firstAuthor="HOLTTUM" journalOrPublisher="Fl. Males." pageId="7" pageNumber="100" pagination="1 - 36" part="1" refId="ref9502" refString="HOLTTUM, R. E. (1959 b). Gleicheniaceae. Fl. Males. ser. 2, 1: 1 - 36." title="Gleicheniaceae" type="journal article" year="1959" yearSuffix="b">HOLTTUM (1959b)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="B5794B65FFB6FFECFAE9FAFA4A05FA95" author="KNAPP" firstAuthor="KNAPP" journalOrPublisher="Gaoshu Township" pageId="7" pageNumber="100" refId="ref9684" refString="KNAPP, R. (2014). Index to Ferns and Fern Allies of Taiwan. Gaoshu Township." title="Index to Ferns and Fern Allies of Taiwan" type="book" year="2014">KNAPP (2014)</bibRefCitation>
cited original material from 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFB6FFECFB22FA9A4D9AFA95" box="[1193,1272,1356,1380]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
or 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFB6FFECFA94FA9A4CECFA95" box="[1311,1422,1356,1380]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
in Herb. Delessert (G). Two collections in G-PREL originated from 
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFB6FFECFCD0FA5A4ACAFA55" box="[859,936,1420,1444]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
[
<collectingCountry id="A9FF7604FFB6FFECFC3EFA5A4D46FA55" box="[949,1060,1420,1444]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="7" pageNumber="100">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
] [G00349562, G00349563]. Both are collections from the Ceylon’s VOC, dated 1773, and cannot be considered as original material.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
